title: Newcastle United vs Chelsea - English Premier League 2024/25 Week 37
description: Newcastle have won seven of their last 11 Premier League home games against Chelsea, including both under manager Eddie Howe. Chelsea have won 31 Premier League games against Newcastle, only beating Tottenham and West Ham more often in the competition.

title: Manchester United vs West Ham United - English Premier League 2024/25 Week 37
description: Manchester United are unbeaten in their last 16 Premier League home games against West Ham, winning each of their last four without conceding. West Ham have won three of their last four Premier League games against Man Utd, as many as in their previous 28 beforehand. They’re looking to complete their first league double over the Red Devils since 2006-07.

description: Liverpool are unbeaten in their last 14 home games against Arsenal in all competitions since a 2-0 loss in the Premier League in September 2012. title: Fulham vs Everton - English Premier League 2024/25 Week 37
description: Fulham are unbeaten in their last six Premier League games against Everton, having only avoided defeat in six of their previous 20 versus the Toffees beforehand. Having lost their first seven Premier League away games against Fulham, Everton have since only lost two of their last 10 league visits to Craven Cottage.

title: AFC Bournemouth vs Aston Villa - English Premier League 2024/25 Week 37
description: Bournemouth lost 1-0 at home to Aston Villa in their first ever Premier League match in August 2015. Since then, the Cherries are unbeaten in three at home to the Villans, scoring exactly two goals in each. Aston Villa are unbeaten in their last four Premier League games against Bournemouth, having lost four in a row against the Cherries before this.

title: Ipswich Town vs Brentford - English Premier League 2024/25 Week 37
description: Ipswich have won just one of their last 10 league games against Brentford, a 2-0 home win in August 2017. This is the first time they’re hosting the Bees since a 1-1 draw in September 2018 in the Championship. Following their 4-3 win at the Gtech Community Stadium in October, Brentford are looking to complete a league double over Ipswich for the first time.

title: Wolverhampton Wanderers vs Brighton and Hove Albion - English Premier League 2024/25 Week 37
description: Having lost just one of their 11 home league games against Brighton between 1991 and 2021, Wolves have now lost each of their last three against the Seagulls at Molineux. Brighton are unbeaten in their last six Premier League games against Wolves, scoring 18 goals during this run.

title: Celta de Vigo vs Sevilla - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 35
description: Celta de Vigo have picked up points in five of their last six LaLiga matches against Sevilla, after losing seven of their previous 11 in the competition. Sevilla have not lost any of their last four away matches against Celta de Vigo in LaLiga, their longest unbeaten run away from home against the Galician side in their top-flight history.

title: Girona vs Villarreal - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 35
description: Girona have only won two of their 11 home matches against Villarreal in all competitions, 2-1 in October 2004 in the Copa del Rey and 2-0 in December 2012 in the LaLiga Hypermotion, losing the remaining nine. Villarreal are one of the three away teams with the most wins at the Municipal de Montilivi in ​​LaLiga, along with Barcelona and Real Betis.

title: Atletico Madrid vs Real Sociedad - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 35
description: Atletico de Madrid have not lost any of their last 10 LaLiga matches against Real Sociedad, since a 0-2 defeat in September 2019, their longest unbeaten run against the San Sebastian side in the competition since April 1976. At home, Atletico de Madrid have not lost in their last 11 LaLiga matches against Real Sociedad, since a 0-1 defeat in March 2013, scoring exactly two goals in six of the last seven.

title: UCL Best Moments of UCL Semi Final
description: All goals and best moments of the UCL semifinal matches season 2024/2025.

title: Barcelona vs Real Madrid - LaLiga 2024/25
description: Barcelona have won their last three matches against Real Madrid in all competitions, only once in the entire history of ElClásico, between 2008 and 2010 under Josep Guardiola, have the Blaugrana managed 4+ consecutive wins. Real Madrid have won four of their last five away matches against FC Barcelona in all competitions, achieving the same number of victories as in their previous 19 visits to Barcelona.

title: Real Betis vs Osasuna - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 35
description: Real Betis have won nine of their last 10 LaLiga matches against Osasuna, scoring in all 10, their longest run of scoring against the Reds in the competitions history. Osasuna have lost their last six away matches against Real Betis in LaLiga, their worst consecutive losing streak against the Betis side in their history in the top-flight.

title: LaLiga Talking Football 2024/2025 Ep.5
description: TALKING FOOTBALL is an exclusive unique window into Spanish football and the people that have made it what it is. We dress as coaches and join their meetings and private discussions. We talk to LALIGA legends in their environment about deep issues, their successes but also their weaknesses. Wed like to lead the media agenda with conversations that you dont normally hear with managers, players and the most recognisable directors. All that presented by Guillem Balague.

title: Las Palmas vs Rayo Vallecano - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 35
description: UD Las Palmas have won their last two LaLiga matches against Rayo Vallecano, the first time they have won two consecutive matches against the red-and-white team in the top-flight. Rayo Vallecano have won their last three LaLiga away matches against UD Las Palmas, keeping a clean sheet in all three, and could become the first team to win four consecutive away matches against the Canary Islands side without conceding in the entire history of the competition.

title: Mallorca vs Real Valladolid - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 35
description: Mallorca have not lost any of their last three LaLiga matches against Real Valladolid, after losing three of their previous four against the Pucelanos in the competition. At home, Mallorca have only lost 9.5% of their LaLiga matches against Real Valladolid, their lowest percentage against a single opponent in at least 12 home matches in the competition.

title: UCL Best Moments of UCL Semi Final
description: All goals and best moments of the UCL semifinal matches season 2024/2025.

title: Valencia vs Getafe - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 35
description: Valencia have won only four of their last 17 LaLiga matches against Getafe, after winning 12 of their previous 16 top-flight matches. Getafe have lost each of their last three LaLiga away matches against Valencia, after picking up points in their previous five visits to Mestalla in the competition.

title: Athletic Bilbao vs Deportivo Alaves - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 35
description: Athletic Club have not lost any of their last six LaLiga matches against Alaves, their second-longest unbeaten run against the Vitoria side in the competition, following their first 14 top-flight clashes. title: Wolfsburg vs Hoffenheim - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 33
description: TSG Hoffenheim and VfL Wolfsburg meet for the third time this season. The Wolves won 3-0 at home in the DFB-Pokal round of 16 at the start of December and also beat TSG 1-0 in Sinsheim in the reverse fixture. VfL could now win three competitive games against the same side in a single season for just the fourth time in professional football. TSG Hoffenheim sit in 15th place having only collected 31 points from 32 games this season – they have only ever claimed fewer points from 32 Bundesliga matchdays in 2012/13. TSG are five points clear of 16th place – since the introduction of three points per win, only 1. FC Nurnberg in 1998/99 have ever blown such an advantage this late on in a season.

title: Eintracht Frankfurt vs St. Pauli - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 33
description: Eintracht Frankfurt, founded in 1899, are now set to play their 1,899th Bundesliga game. They are still unbeaten in their six home matches against St. Pauli and have only hosted RB Leipzig more often in the top flight without ever losing. Eintracht Frankfurt are unbeaten in their last 14 Bundesliga games against promoted sides, winning each of the last four. They now have the chance to equal two club records: a five-game winning streak against promoted teams from 1991 under Dragoslav Stepanovic and a 15-match undefeated run against them between 2008 and 2012.

title: Bundesliga - Special 2024/2025 - Roots: Kane, Schick and Ekitike
description: Three strikers, three stories, one common goal: scoring goals for the teams success. But what shaped Harry Kane, Patrik Schick, and Hugo Ekitike on their paths to the top? In the 26-minute documentary Roots – Kane, Schick and Ekitike, we travel back to the beginnings of these Bundesliga stars. For FC Bayern Munchen player Harry Kane, we trace his roots in Chingford, a suburban town in East London. We also speak with youth coaches from his first club, Ridgeway Rovers, as well as former Tottenham player and England international Jermain Defoe. title: Bayer Leverkusen vs Borussia Dortmund - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 33
description: After winning the reverse fixture, Bayer 04 Leverkusen could now do a league double over Borussia Dortmund for the first time since 2006/07. However, their three-game wait at home for a victory against BVB in the Bundesliga is currently their longest against any top-flight side. Bayer 04 Leverkusen are unbeaten in their last seven Bundesliga games – only Union Berlin are currently enjoying a longer undefeated spell. However, B04’s 2-2 draw in Freiburg was their third draw in their last four games and their 11th overall in 2024/25, a joint league high together with RB Leipzig. Since 2000, the Werkself have only ever shared the points more often in a season in 2009/10.

title: Stuttgart vs Augsburg - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 33
description: VfB Stuttgart are unbeaten in their last seven competitive games against FC Augsburg, winning each of the last four without conceding a single goal. VfB won the most recent meeting 1-0 at home in the quarter-finals of the DFB-Pokal on 4th February 2025. Only FC Bayern have created more big chances this season than VfB Stuttgart, whereas FC Augsburg have had the fewest in the league – not even half as many as VfB.

title: Werder Bremen vs RB Leipzig - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 33
description: RB Leipzig are unbeaten in their last 10 competitive games against SV Werder Bremen, winning eight of them. Of teams currently in the top flight that they have faced more than four times, Leipzig’s points-per-game average against SVW isn’t higher against any other side. SV Werder Bremen sit in eighth place with 47 points – they last had more points after 32 Bundesliga games in 2009/10 when they last qualified for Europe. SVW are three points behind sixth-placed RB Leipzig – since the introduction of three points per win, only Karlsruher SC in 1996/97 and Hamburger SV in 1995/96 have ever made up as large a gap to sixth over the last two matchdays.

title: Bochum vs Mainz 05 - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 33
description: VfL Bochum average just 0.38 points per Bundesliga game against 1. FSV Mainz 05, their lowest return against any team. Only VfL Wolfsburg are currently on a longer wait for a Bundesliga win than VfL Bochum and 1. FSV Mainz 05. This is Mainz’s longest spell without victory since between November 2023 and February 2024.

The 2025 Formula One season will feature 10 teams, 20 drivers, and a record 24 races across 21 countries, marking the championships 75th anniversary. All race weekends, including every Practice, Qualifying, Sprint and Race will be live and exclusive on beIN.

title: Race 1 - Formula 4 Italy - Misano Round - 2025
description: The 2025 Italian F4 Championship roars to life at the Misano World Circuit. In Race 1, a grid packed with ambitious young talent takes to the track for the seasons opening battle. With nerves high and margins tight, every move counts in the quest for early momentum and points.

title: Race 2 - Formula 4 Italy - Misano Round - 2025
description: Race 2 of the Misano weekend intensifies the fight for supremacy in the Italian F4 Championship. Drivers adjust strategies and sharpen their focus after Race 1, aiming to climb the standings in a fast-paced, highly tactical contest under pressure.

title: Race 3 - Formula 4 Italy - Misano Round - 2025
description: The final showdown at Misano sees the field go all out in Race 3, where consistency and courage could decide the weekend’s overall winner. With podiums and crucial points at stake, expect a dramatic and decisive finale in this opening round of the 2025 season.

title: Race 4 - Formula 4 Italy - Misano Round - 2025
description: Closing the Misano round, Race 4 delivers one final chance for drivers to make their mark. With track conditions changing and fatigue setting in, precision and boldness will determine who finishes strong in this extended weekend of thrilling junior formula action.

title: Sprint Race - France GP - Moto GP
description: The sixth round of the 2025 MotoGP season features the Tissot Sprint Race at Le Mans iconic Bugatti Circuit. Top riders like Marc Márquez, Álex Márquez, and Francesco Bagnaia compete in this high-intensity, half-distance race, aiming to secure valuable championship points ahead of Sundays main event. Expect thrilling overtakes and fierce competition as the championship battle intensifies.

title: Main Race - France Round- Moto 3
description: The lightweight class lines up for the main race at the iconic Le Mans circuit. Riders tackle 22 laps of high-intensity action, with close slipstreaming and bold overtakes expected throughout. Precision, bravery, and race craft will define the battle for victory and championship points.

title: Main Race - France Round - Moto 2
description: The intermediate class takes center stage at Le Mans for the sixth round of the 2025 season. Riders will navigate 22 laps of the 4.2 km Bugatti Circuit, aiming to master its technical layout and secure vital championship points. Expect intense competition and strategic overtakes as the Moto2 field battles for supremacy on this iconic French track.

title: Main Race - France GP - Moto GP
description: The premier class of motorcycle racing returns to the iconic Le Mans Bugatti Circuit for Round 6 of the season. Riders battle over 27 laps on the technical 4.2 km layout, known for its tight corners and unpredictable conditions. Expect high-speed duels, bold overtakes, and fierce competition as the championship fight intensifies in front of passionate French fans.

description: Explore the sporting secrets of F1. Across 25 episodes and in crisp 3D animations, we analyses the technical details, which decide which teams make the most of the rules - and which need to go back to the drawing board. Complemented by features on historical milestones as well as race previews - GP Confidential is the perfect treat for any F1 fan.

description: Volleyball is a renowned sport and game and Its impact has grown over the world. The Qatar foundation made a deal with the international volleyball federation to create the volleyball foundation in the fifth continent. The goal of this project is to merge volleyball and social society to help the future generation to access this sport.

description: Algiers hosted the last Olympic African Committee and it was a great opportunity to meet with the last Olympic Champions of Paris 2024 from different sports. What will be future strategy of ACNOA as leader sports organization in the International Olympic movement.

title: Athletics Grand Slam Track - Miami - Day 1
description: The Miami leg of the Athletics Grand Slam begins with an explosive Day 1, featuring opening heats and qualifying rounds across sprints, hurdles, and field events. Top athletes aim to set the tone and secure early positions in the chase for gold.

title: Athletics Grand Slam Track - Miami - Day 2
description: Day 2 brings rising intensity as semi-finals and key field event finals unfold. Sprinters, throwers, and jumpers push to their limits in pursuit of Grand Slam points, as the competition heats up under the Miami sun.

title: Athletics Grand Slam Track - Miami - Day 3
description: The final day of action in Miami delivers dramatic medal showdowns and high-stakes finishes across multiple disciplines. With champions to be crowned and records on the line, Day 3 promises peak performances and unforgettable moments.

title: CHI Al Shaqab - 2025 – Grand Prix Final Summary
description: In this highlights program, the world’s top riders — Olympic gold, silver, and bronze medalists, along with the highest-ranked athletes — gather for the 2025 CHI AL SHAQAB International Show Jumping Championship. Set against the stunning backdrop of Doha, the event showcases outstanding performances and fierce rivalries, reflecting the power, precision, and elegance of elite equestrian sport.

title: Summary of the Global Tour Show Jumping Championship - Doha Round
description: This highlights program captures the electrifying atmosphere of the Longines Global Champions Tour in Doha — a critical stop for riders and teams chasing maximum points. Across three days of world-class competition, the best riders on the planet battled fiercely, with the Grand Prix Final delivering unforgettable moments at the heart of one of the most prestigious stages of the season.

title: Al Ahli (KSA) vs Kawasaki (JPN) - AFC Champions League Elite 2024/25 - Final
description: Al-Ahli will face Kawasaki Frontale for the first time in the AFC Champions League elite and for the first time against a Japanese team. Conversely, this will be Kawasaki Frontales second encounter against a Saudi team after defeating Al-Nassr 3-2 in the semi-finals. Al-Ahli have won only once in 5 matches against East Asian teams, with the win against Shenzhen 2-1 in the 2005 quarter-finals. This will be the fourth final between a Saudi team and a Japanese team in the AFC Champions League elite, the most common final matchup in the tournament. All previous finals were between Al-Hilal and Urawa Red Diamonds, with Al-Hilal winning one title in 2019 and Urawa winning two titles in 2017 and 2

title: Al Ahli Road to the AFC title 2024/25
description: Al Ahli celebrated becoming only the third Saudi club to win the Champions League, after record four-time winners Al Hilal and two-time champions Al Ittihad. Al Ahli have been crowned champions of Asia at the third attempt. Watch in this program how Al Ahli won the title.

title: My Faith in Sport - Sawm
description: Ramadan is a crucial period in the Islamic calendar but fasting (Sawm) can provide complications for athletes who are trying to compete at the highest level. But to what extent is fasting a negative or can it actually aid performance? We look at the life and adaptation throughout Ramadan of Adam Azim – an unbeaten professional boxer from the UK, Fares El Bakh – a weightlifter who won Qatar’s first ever Olympic gold medal, and Zainab Alema – a rugby player who is aiming to become the first player to represent England wearing a hijab. Experts in Sports Science and Nutrition from Aspetar Clinic, Qatar also add detail of the physical impact athletes encounter during Ramadan.

With a month-long waiting period, the competition will take place during the strongest day of Tramontana. So put April in your diaries for what will be a memorable second Big Air World Cup event.

title: World Chess Show 2025
description: Episode three of The World Chess Show looks at some of the hot topics in chess at the moment and asks whether the growth of the game online and the shorter formats threaten the classical format. We also review the all-Chinese Women’s World Championship match between Ju Wenjun and Tan Zhongyi as well as meeting two young women flying the flag for India in Vaishali R and Divya Deshmukh. We also head to Spain to find out how a chess board is made. Our match analysis comes from a TATA Steel classic between Nodirbek Abdusattorov and Jorden van Foreest and we also challenge Jorden to a quickfire QandA against the clock.
